    <p class="case-section__label">// about</p>
    <h2 class="case-section__title">About</h2>
    <p>Vermont Academy is a small independent boarding school in southern Vermont. For six years, I taught Filmmaking, Graphic Design, and Digital Photography to high school students while also serving as a dorm parent, multi-sport coach, and student adviser.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section" data-animate>
    <p class="case-section__label">// teaching</p>
    <h2 class="case-section__title">Teaching</h2>
    <p>I designed and taught courses in filmmaking, graphic design, and digital photography — building curricula from scratch and mentoring students through hands-on creative projects. The work went beyond the classroom: I coached multiple sports, lived on campus as a dorm parent, and served as a student adviser. In 2016, the school community awarded me the <strong>Barbara Sweet Teacher of the Year Award</strong>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section" data-animate>
    <p class="case-section__label">// communications</p>
    <h2 class="case-section__title">Communications</h2>
    <p>Alongside teaching, I served as an assistant to the Communications Office, creating video, photography, design, and promotional content for the school. I also designed the yearbook for all six years. This dual role — educator and communicator — taught me how to listen to an institution's identity and translate it into visual stories that connect.</p>
  </section>

